liblogging
------------------------------------------
Liblogging offers an enhanced replacement for the syslog() call, but retains
its ease of use. In a nutshell, it permits sytem administrators to direct
application log output to different destinations without requiring the app
developer to do any work for this. Liblogging is released under a 2-clause BSD
license and as such can be used in any application.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.6-1
  liblogging-devel-1.0.8-1bl1
  liblogging0-1.0.8-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cygport-0.37.6-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2
  python39-docutils-0.22.4-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/rsyslog/liblogging

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/rsyslog/liblogging/archive/refs/tags/v1.0.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack liblogging-1.0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./liblogging-1.0.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/liblogging-1.0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblogging-1.0.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblogging0-1.0.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblogging-devel-1.0.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(liblogging)
  /usr/bin/stdlogctl.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/liblogging.README
  /usr/share/doc/liblogging/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/liblogging/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/liblogging/HISTORY.md
  /usr/share/doc/liblogging/README
  /usr/share/doc/liblogging/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/stdlogctl.1.gz

(liblogging0)
  /usr/bin/cyglogging-rfc3195-0.dll
  /usr/bin/cyglogging-stdlog-0.dll

(liblogging-devel)
  /usr/include/liblogging/liblogging.h
  /usr/include/liblogging/settings.h
  /usr/include/liblogging/srAPI.h
  /usr/include/liblogging/stdlog.h
  /usr/include/liblogging/syslogmessage.h
  /usr/lib/liblogging-rfc3195.dll.a
  /usr/lib/liblogging-stdlog.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/liblogging-rfc3195.pc
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/liblogging-stdlog.pc
  /usr/share/man/man3/stdlog.3.gz

